Television viewers will have a rare opportunity of an insight into the mind of Olu of Warri, Ogiame Atuwatse 3 when he features on this weekend’s edition of CNN African Voices Changemakers. Programme sponsor and digital solutions provider, Globacom, disclosed in a statement on Friday that Olu Atuwatse will be the special guest on the show which airs on DSTV Channel 401 at  9.30 a.m. on Saturday.  Repeats of the edition will be aired on Sunday at 4.30 a.m, 7.30 a.m, 12.30 p.m, 7.30 p.m and on Monday at 4.00 a.m. while a two-part, 15-minute rebroadcast comes up on Tuesday and Wednesday at 6.45 p.m. Atuwatse who became the Olu of Warri in August 2021 was born in 1984 as Tsola Emiko. He is a graduate of International Studies and Political Science from Case Western Reserve University, Cleveland, Ohio, USA, and also obtained a Master of Science degree in management from the same university. He uses his platform to establish new projects and create new employment opportunities and business ideas for his subjects who are made up of a large number of youths with talents in the creative arts and entertainment. He will be joined on the 30-minute magazine programme by Sabrina Elba, model, actor and rights activist of Kenyan descent. Elba, on her part, reconnects with her African roots by assisting small-scale farmers with funds in order to expand their farms and enhance their yields and profits.